    <!-- 植物养护指南页面 (通过ID引用实现，实际项目中应为独立页面) -->
    <section id="care-guide" class="care-guide">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">Plant Care Guide</h2>
            <p>Learn how to care for your plants and keep them healthy and vibrant all year round.</p>
            
            <!-- 养护指南分类 -->
            <div class="care-categories">
                <button class="care-category active" data-category="watering">Watering Tips</button>
                <button class="care-category" data-category="fertilizing">Fertilizing</button>
                <button class="care-category" data-category="pruning">Pruning</button>
                <button class="care-category" data-category="pests">Pest Control</button>
            </div>
            
            <!-- 养护指南内容 -->
            <div class="care-content" id="watering-content">
                <h3>Watering Tips for Healthy Plants</h3>
                <p>Proper watering is essential for the health of your plants. Here are some tips to help you water your plants correctly:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Water deeply but infrequently to encourage deep root growth</li>
                    <li>Water in the morning or evening to reduce evaporation</li>
                    <li>Avoid wetting the leaves, as this can lead to fungal diseases</li>
                    <li>Check the soil moisture before watering - stick your finger 1-2 inches into the soil; if it's dry, it's time to water</li>
                    <li>Different plants have different water needs - research the specific needs of your plants</li>
                </ul>
                <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/156/600/300" alt="Watering plants">
            </div>
            
            <div class="care-content hidden" id="fertilizing-content">
                <h3>Fertilizing Your Plants</h3>
                <p>Fertilizing provides essential nutrients to your plants, helping them grow strong and healthy. Here's what you need to know:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Use a balanced fertilizer for most plants, or a specialized fertilizer for specific needs</li>
                    <li>Fertilize during the growing season (spring and summer) and reduce or stop in fall and winter</li>
                    <li>Follow the instructions on the fertilizer package to avoid over-fertilizing, which can damage roots</li>
                    <li>Organic fertilizers are a great option for sustainable gardening</li>
                </ul>
                <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/157/600/300" alt="Fertilizing plants">
            </div>
            
            <div class="care-content hidden" id="pruning-content">
                <h3>Pruning Techniques</h3>
                <p>Pruning helps maintain the shape of your plants and promotes healthy growth
